			<div class="content" id="post-content-1021400">
									

<p>It's certainly not what I'd pick :P</p>
<p>The point is that it's not <em>presented</em> as a code name. It's just tossed out there, like, oh hey, here's this dude, opus. They called him possum in high school, yup.</p>
<p>I know kids on this site well enough to know that if someone posted an article referencing "Doctor XxW1ngxPr0xX" kids would flip the hell out. Thing is, names like "opus" and "trebuchet" and "blast" and "spazztique Z" and such are just as impossible to take seriously.</p>
<p>The question is, where do we draw the line, and how willing are we to enforce it? I'm tired of seeing silly names around the place, yo.</p>

